            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-nduja-and-pepper-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-nduja-and-pepper-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>sliced pepper </strong>and<strong> 'Nduja </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 5-6 min or until the pepper is softened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-nduja-and-pepper-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>tomato & mozzarella tortelloni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tortelloni</strong> for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> cooked tortelloni </strong>in a colander, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-nduja-and-pepper-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-nduja-and-pepper-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the peppers are softened, add your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>balsamic sundried tomato paste </strong>and <strong>cooked tortelloni </strong>with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>and gently stir it all together</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato & mozzarella tortelloni with creamy 'Nduja & pepper sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy cooking water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
